Preheat the #oven{} to 450 degrees.

> If you're making this recipe in advance, take the pizza dough out of the fridge so
> it can come to room temperature ahead of time - it'll be so much easier to roll out!

Using your hands, stretch out the @pizza dough{10%ounce} into a rough 1/4-inch thick
rectangle. Place onto a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}, and prick all over with a
#fork{}. Place in the oven for ~{8-10%minutes}, until beginning to brown on the edges.

> If you have a rolling pin or wine bottle, you can use it to roll out the dough on
> a lightly floured surface.

Wash and dry all produce. Meanwhile, thinly slice the @prosciutto{4%ounce}. Halve the
@heirloom grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Thinly slice the @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce}.

When the dough is lightly golden brown, spread it with about 3 Tablespoons
@pesto{4%ounce}. Top with the mozzarella, tomatoes and prosciutto. Return to the oven
for ~{5-6%minutes}, until the cheese melts and the prosciutto crisps.

Remove the flatbread from the oven, and drizzle lightly with @olive oil{2%teaspoon}.
Let rest for a moment before cutting into squares. Enjoy!